Title: EXTERIOR PANELS / TRIM: REAR BUMPER: DISASSEMBLY; 2019 - 2022 MY Prius [12/2018 -        ]

DISASSEMBLY

PROCEDURE

1. REMOVE REAR SIDE ULTRASONIC SENSOR (w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System)

Click here

2. REMOVE REAR CORNER ULTRASONIC SENSOR (w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System)

Click here

3. REMOVE REAR CENTER ULTRASONIC SENSOR (w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System)

Click here

4. REMOVE REAR SIDE ULTRASONIC SENSOR RETAINER (w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System)

Click here

5. REMOVE REAR CORNER ULTRASONIC SENSOR RETAINER (w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System)

Click here

6. REMOVE REAR CENTER ULTRASONIC SENSOR RETAINER (w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System)

Click here

7. REMOVE NO. 2 REAR COMBINATION LIGHT ASSEMBLY LH

Click here

8. REMOVE NO. 2 REAR COMBINATION LIGHT ASSEMBLY RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

9. REMOVE NO. 3 LUGGAGE ROOM WIRE

(a) w/o Intuitive Parking Assist System:

(1) Disengage the 10 clamps and remove the No. 3 luggage room wire.

(b) w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System:

(1) Disengage the 16 clamps and remove the No. 3 luggage room wire.

10. REMOVE ULTRASONIC SENSOR CLIP

(a) w/o Intuitive Parking Assist System:

(1) Remove the 2 ultrasonic sensor clips.

(b) w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System:

(1) Remove the 6 ultrasonic sensor clips.

11. REMOVE LOWER REAR BUMPER COVER

(a) Disengage the 2 claws as shown in the illustration.

*a

Hook

Remove in this Direction

(b) Disengage the hook to remove the lower rear bumper cover.

12. REMOVE REFLEX REFLECTOR ASSEMBLY LH

(a) Remove the screw.

(b) Disengage the claw and guide to remove the reflex reflector assembly LH.

13. REMOVE REFLEX REFLECTOR ASSEMBLY RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

14. REMOVE CENTER REAR BUMPER GUARD

(a) Remove the 6 clips.

(b) Disengage the 10 claws and 6 guides as shown in the illustration to remove the center rear bumper guard.

Remove in this Direction

-

-

15. REMOVE NO. 1 REAR BUMPER PAD

(a) Remove the No. 1 rear bumper pad.

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

16. REMOVE NO. 2 REAR BUMPER PAD

(a) Remove the No. 2 rear bumper pad.

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

17. REMOVE REAR BUMPER ARM SEAL

(a) Remove the rear bumper arm seal.

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

18. REMOVE NO. 3 REAR BUMPER PAD

(a) Remove the No. 3 rear bumper pad.

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

19. REMOVE CENTER REAR BUMPER PAD

(a) Remove the center rear bumper pad.

20. REMOVE REAR BUMPER SIDE RETAINER LH

(a) Disengage the 3 clips as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction

(b) Disengage the guide as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction (1)

Remove in this Direction (2)

(c) Disengage the claw as shown in the illustration to remove the rear bumper side retainer LH.

21. REMOVE REAR BUMPER SIDE RETAINER RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

22. REMOVE REAR BUMPER SIDE SEAL LH

(a) Remove the rear bumper side clip.

*1

Rear Bumper Side Clip

(b) Remove the 3 clips and rear bumper side seal LH.

23. REMOVE REAR BUMPER SIDE SEAL RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

24. REMOVE NO. 1 REAR BUMPER REINFORCEMENT

(a) Remove the 6 bolts and No. 1 rear bumper reinforcement.

25. REMOVE REAR BUMPER ARM SUB-ASSEMBLY LH

(a) Remove the 4 bolts and rear bumper arm sub-assembly LH.

26. REMOVE REAR BUMPER ARM SUB-ASSEMBLY RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.
